Pinellas County Schools
August 28 at 2:08 PM ¬∑

Congressman Charlie Crist paid a visit to Largo High School to present students and staff with a display from the National Archives in Washington, DC commemorating the 100th anniversary of the passage of the 19th Amendment to the US Constitution, which ended gender-based voting restrictions in the US.

This visit and presentation commended the students, who started a school-based effort last year to register eligible students to vote, for their work in increasing youth voter turnout and breaking down voting barriers. Students plan to continue efforts this year.

Congressman Charlie Crist paid a visit to Largo High School to present students and staff with a display from the National Archives in Washington, DC commemorating the 100th anniversary of the passage of the 19th Amendment to the US Constitution, which ended gender-based voting restrictions in the US.

post_text: ¬°Somos #PCSProud para compartir que Lexi se dirige a la Florida Atlantic University para estudiar negocios!
shared_text:
Tiffany Davies is with Lexi Davies.
May 1 at 2:00 PM ¬∑

Well, it is decision day. Lexi has made the tough decision to hang up her cleats and focus on her education. Pinellas County Schools

She was accepted to every school she applied to and had offers to play at two private schools (with scholarships) and made the very mature decision to go to a bigger school with higher accreditation.

This fall she will be at Florida Atlantic University in Boca Raton Florida studying business. She will get to experience going away to school, meeting a lot of new people, and being a college kid. Of course, there will be intramural sports and she hopes to get involved with the football team (on the sidelines, not as a player).

#FAU
#DecisionDay
#PCSDecisionDay
#Classof2020

Go Owls!
